// The expected prompts below were generated by running the reference
// Python implementation (scribe/analyzer.py's build_prompt) with the same
// arguments; BuildPrompt must reproduce them byte-for-byte.

const expectedPromptFull = `You are analyzing a meeting transcript to distill it into a personal knowledge library.

First, read the meeting transcript from this file using your file reading tool: /tmp/proj/.state/tmp/transcript-abc123.txt
Base your entire analysis on its contents.

The knowledge library already contains these topics (slug: name):
- go-migration: Go Migration
- obs-setup: OBS Setup
REUSE an existing slug whenever the subject of a topic matches. Only create a new slug for genuinely new subjects.

Respond with ONLY a valid JSON object (no prose, no markdown fences) matching exactly this schema:
{
  "meeting": {
    "title": "short descriptive title",
    "summary": "2-4 sentence summary of the meeting",
    "key_points": ["point 1", "point 2"],
    "decisions": ["decision 1"],
    "action_items": [{"owner": "person name or 'unassigned'", "task": "what must be done"}]
  },
  "topics": [
    {
      "slug": "kebab-case-slug",
      "name": "Human readable name",
      "content": "Markdown with what was newly learned about this topic in this meeting"
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
- Slugs must be lowercase kebab-case, ASCII, no accents.
- "content" of each topic is Markdown: what was newly learned about that topic in THIS meeting (facts, decisions, context), not a meeting summary.
- 1 to 5 topics, each focused on a single subject.
- Write ALL output (title, summary, key points, decisions, action items, topic names and content) in the same language as the transcript ("en").
- If a list would be empty, use an empty array.
- Your final message must contain ONLY the JSON object, nothing else.
`

